<title>USA: Intl Remote sees 1996 loss.</title>
<headline>Intl Remote sees 1996 loss.</headline>
<dateline>CHATSWORTH, Calif. 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>International Remote Imaging Systems Inc expects to report a pretax loss of $10.9 million for 1996, compared with a pretax loss last year of $1.5 million.</p>
<p>It said it has not yet determined its provision for income tax benefit.</p>
<p>The company also said its net sales for 1996 rose to $20.6 million from $14.4 million last year.</p>
<p>It said the loss stems largely from $7.3 million in acquisition expenses for the purchase of the PowerGene business of Perceptive Scientific Instruments.</p>
